Program: Omnibus
Title: Underground Railroad, Slavery
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376lpg
Last Broadcast Date: 06 May 1998
Stories of the journeys taken by runaway slaves in the southern states of the US as told to William Still who wrote up 900 accounts of underground railroad escapes in 1872. Contributors include Charles Blockson whose great grandfather Jim was one escapee.